Alembic migrations for llama-service.

This repository is in clean-slate migration mode for non-production/test environments.
Old revision history is intentionally not preserved.

Required env vars:
- DATABASE_URL (app runtime URL, often asyncpg)
- ALEMBIC_DATABASE_URL (sync URL used by Alembic)

Standard flow:
1) Reset test database schema:
   DROP SCHEMA public CASCADE; CREATE SCHEMA public;
2) Remove old revision files from alembic/versions/*.py
   (PowerShell: Remove-Item alembic/versions/*.py)
3) Generate new initial migration:
   alembic revision --autogenerate -m "initial clean schema"
4) Inspect generated migration:
   rg -n "create_table|create_index|ForeignKeyConstraint|UniqueConstraint|drop_table|drop_index" alembic/versions/*_initial_clean_schema.py
5) Apply migration:
   alembic upgrade head
6) Verify:
   alembic current
   alembic check

Do not use `scripts/init_db.py` as migration source of truth.
Schema lifecycle must go through Alembic revisions.
